Gauteng hospitals are seeing a significant drop in new COVID-19 admissions. The province recorded the highest number of admissions mid-July. Acting Gauteng Health MEC Jacob Mamabolo discusses the situation with eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The COVID-19 storm is closing in on Gauteng, according to acting Health MEC Jacob Mamabolo. The province is expected to see a drastic increase in coronavirus cases between the last week of August and early September. COVID-19: Mamabolo says too early to celebrate drop in hospital admissions Mamabolo unpacked the situation, saying adhering to lockdown regulations is crucial to curbing the spread of COVID-19. He promised the Gauteng government will crack down on risky behaviour. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.